license: CC-BY-4.0
keywords:
  - water pollution
  - agriculture
  - Canada
  - polluter-pays
  - farmland consolidation
  - phosphorus
  - nutrient management
abstract: >-
  Three independent research papers on agricultural water pollution in Canada.
  Paper 1 estimates fiscal incidence of water-pollution management costs.
  Paper 2 examines how farmland consolidation raises enforcement and recovery risk
  for large title holders. Paper 3 frames food-price pass-through and social
  cost–benefit incidence.
